content.body:
## Shop 205/60R16 Tire Size 205/60R16 tires are commonly used on sedans and smaller crossovers, such as the Mazda 3, Volkswagen Jetta, Nissan Sentra, Ford EcoSport, Hyundai Kona, or Kia Niro. A brand new version of any of these vehicles will often roll out of the factory with a set of all-season tires such as the Continental ProContact TX, Hankook Kinergy GT (H436), Firestone FT140, [Bridgestone Ecopia EP422 Plus](https://simpletire.com/brands/bridgestone-tires/ecopia-ep422-plus), Nexen CP461, or Michelin Energy Saver A/S attached thanks to their ability to perform at a high level year-round. Popular vehicles: 2014-2021 Mazda3
2019-2021 Volkswagen Jetta
2020-2021 Nissan Sentra
2018-2021 Ford EcoSport
2018-2022 Hyundai Kona
2017-2021 Kia Niro All-season tires are the most commonly used tires in the U.S. thanks to their ability to perform well in dry, wet, and light winter weather conditions. If you’re looking for a new set of 205/60R16 all-season tires that aren’t original equipment for your ride, check out the Pirelli P4 Four Seasons Plus, Nokian One, [Yokohama Avid Ascend GT](https://simpletire.com/brands/yokohama-tires/avid-ascend-gt), or Falken Ziex ZE960 A/S. All-weather tires are quickly increasing in popularity, as they blend dry and wet performance of an all-season tire with the winter traction of a winter tire. If you live in an area that gets moderate to heavy snow, you might want to consider a set of best-in-class all-weather tires like the Michelin Cross Climate2 A/W, Firestone WeatherGrip, [General Altimax 365AW](”https://simpletire.com/brands/general-tires/altimax-365AW), or Hankook Kinergy 4S2 (H750) for your car. Do you live in an area that gets heavy ice and snow? While all-season and all-weather tires will help most drivers in winter weather, some might need or want to purchase a set of winter tires that will be a bit more flexible in lower temperatures for consistent traction and performance. Take a look at theContinental VikingContact 7, [Kumho WinterCraft WP72](https://simpletire.com/brands/kumho-tires/wintercraft-wp72), Toyo Observe GSI-5, or Nitto NT-SN2 if you need a tire that’s built to tackle ice, slush, and snow. Whether you drive a Mazda 3, Nissan Sentra, Hyundai Kona or something else, SimpleTire has a set of 205/60R16 tires that meets your needs at a great price!
